	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				The Glacier Bear. This Large bear, a virtual twin to Iceberg is indeed a rare spawn. My adopted sister,Uggla Doomwalker, a 42nd Level Ogre Shaman began camping the bear for the pelt a little befor 2am EST Sunday Morning on the Veeshan Server. We had done a fair amount of research before hand and knew that an Icebone Skeleton was the place holder..and that after he was dispatch, a few minutes later either the Glacier Bear or the false spawn of ANOTHER Icebone would pop. This was supposed to occur every 6 to 8 RL hours. The PlaceHolder popped shortly after our arrival and we killed it. Then came the second Icebone, we killed it and waited. Approximately 7 hours later....a little after 9am...the PH came again. Process repeated, still no Bear. So...we camped and came back in 6 hours. Again, after about an hour, the PH popped and after his death, yet another Icebone. With Uggla staying in the cave and myself venturing out for a bit of air and supplies on occasion, we continually camped the bear, logging in every 6 hours, waiting, killing, logging off in disappointment. The eighth, yes eighth time of this at about 3:15am EST Tuesday, I killed the PH, and the next Icebone. In dejection I went to bed. Uggla logged in about 5am to wait and saw the Servers would be going down at 10am our time, the time for the next spawn, and decided to just go to bed an sleep since neither of us had gotten much of that commodity since Friday night. She did a shout in the ZONE saying how she'd camped the Bear for 50+hrs and now he wasnt due again until the Server Shutdown and she was going to miss him, before she logged off. She awoke at 9:45am our time with a 'lucky feeling' and logged on as I still slept. Just befor 10am the PH popped. She killed it. Within 2 minutes her Sense Animals spell, which had gotten quite a workout over the last 63 hours finally picked up....the Glacier Bear. I was awakened immediatly by here shouts in the next room and jumped up to log on and help..even though she could have handled it, after 3days of sheer mind numbing bordom, I wanted to see the BEAR. I couldnt get on because so many people were leaving for the shutdown, so I had to watch on her screen. The bear was meandering downt he corridor toward the Hut with the 3 stationary Icebones and she was trying to get spell off on it before the Lich of Miragul came wandering around on his neverending march. She hit him with a dot and began melee, she was caught off guard and no pet, and in the excitement hadnt thought to root first..but FINALLY....the payoff for 63 hours of camping was at hand. The Bear wandered into the room with the hut as Ug stayed on him poking numerous holes with her spear, she had done a little over a 'Bubbles' worth of damage and had taken a bit over 100hps in damage herself. As the bear entered the room, a troll shaman who was green to Ug and a Druid in Wolf form named Danao who was Red jumped the Bear. As Uggla fought on the Shaman sat down and the druid began chain blastin with his DD spell of choice. The bear dropped, the Troll Shaman looted the corpse and they gated out. The Troll shaman, who had a rather long name was in the Zone when Ug did her shout about the Bear spawning as the servers went down, and it appeared both the Druid and Troll were played by the same person. Maybe they had pulled the bear with snare befor Ug hit it..maybe not...but in the 63 hours that we sat in that dismal boring cave (on and off yes, but at every spawn, 9 spawns in a row) did we see either one of them. Neither said a word during the short fight with the bear, when they looted it, or as Ug sat down and began to cry, in that cave in make believe game, or here in our own RL home. <BR>
<BR>
      I relate this story to let others know what they are in for when they decide to 'camp' the Glacier Bear. The time, the boredom, the frustration. Also because I felt like getting it off my chest, and to see if anyone can imagine the sense of disappointment, futility, anger, ect at the outcome of our &quot;Quest&quot;. I doubt I will ever undertake another quest during my EQ career. I play this game for enjoyment, and I have to say I have had NO enjoyment from it for nearly 3 days. Between verants idea that an 'Epic Quest' consists of hour upon hour of sitting, and the turn of events at the last spawn, I really dont know if I will ever enjoy the Norrath again as I have in the past.  Thank you for listening to our story and little rant. Feel free to add any comments ect...perhaps knowing we're not alone in our thoughts and poor luck will make the happenings a little more bearable.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
                     Lorgun Bel'Dragon of the<BR>
                         Wolves of the North.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
